[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

In the 24 hours since the last WHO update:
-----------------------------------------
The Americas region reported 54.2% of the global newly reported cases and 68.5% of newly reported fatalities for this 24-hour period. Brazil reported 41.7% of the newly confirmed cases in the region, USA reported 30.0%, Mexico 6.4%, Chile 5.8%, and Peru 4.9%. The same 5 countries remained at the top with Mexico switching order with Chile.

The European region reported 13.4% of the global newly reported cases and 11.6% of the newly confirmed deaths in the region. Russia reported 41.9% of the regional newly reported cases, followed by Sweden 7.8%, Turkey 6.9%, the UK 6.4%, Ukraine 4.8%, and Belarus and Armenia at 3.3% each. Again, same countries, minor juggling of orders and percentages on a daily basis.

The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 13.4% of the global newly reported cases and 9.0% of global newly reported fatalities. Pakistan reported 25.8% of the regional newly reported cases followed by Saudi Arabia 24.8%, Iran 13.6%, Iraq 7.6%, Qatar 6.6%, Egypt 6.4%, and Oman 3.9%. Same countries, minor juggling of positions.

The African region reported 4.7% of the global newly reported cases and 2.2% of newly reported fatalities. South Africa reported 52.4% of the newly reported cases in the region in the past 24 hours, followed by Nigeria 11.2%, Cote d'Ivoire 5.7%, Ghana 5.1%, Kenya 3.2%, Congo DR 2.8%, Guinea 2.6%, Ethiopia 2.9%, and Mauritania 2.5%. While South Africa and Nigeria are consistently number 1 and number 2 in terms of 24-hour increase in cases, other countries have less consistent reporting patterns and vary considerably from day to day.

The Western Pacific region reported 0.72% of the global newly reported cases and 0.16% of global fatalities. The Philippines reported 54.6% of the newly reported cases in the region, followed by Singapore 25.0%, Japan 7.0%, South Korea 4.8%, and China 3.6%. The outbreak associated with the Beijing Seafood markets continues to bring China to prominence in terms of daily newly confirmed cases. That said, the Philippines and Singapore are consistently number 1 and number 2, respectively, and the other countries vary in daily reporting, including Malaysia and Australia.

The South East Asia region reported 13.7% of the global newly reported cases and 8.5% of global fatalities. India reported 69.8% of newly reported cases in the region, followed by Bangladesh 19.5%, Indonesia 6.8%, and Nepal 3.4%. Same countries, same order as in previous days.

Impression: Europe seems to be stabilizing at a significantly lower rate, although Russia is still reporting 7000+ new cases a day (down from 8000+ per day). The Eastern Mediterranean is on par with the European region, with Pakistan reporting 4000+ cases a day and Saudi Arabia reporting 4000+ cases a day. South East Asia surpassed both the European and Eastern Mediterranean regions, with India reporting 8000-10 000+ cases a day. The Americas region is reporting around 70 000 cases a day, with Brazil usually reporting 25 000-30 000+ cases a day and the USA at 20 000-25 000+ a day. In the Africa region, the regional proportion is slowly climbing, with South Africa reporting in the 3000-4000+ range daily, and in the Western Pacific region, they are maintaining a very low rate compared with the other regions, with the Philippines averaging 400+ cases per day (Singapore had been reporting twice as many cases per day for a period of time but has dropped back over the past couple of weeks).

Figure 2. Epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases, by date of report and WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 19 Jun 2020, at the source URL above, is an excellent representation of the epidemic starting in the Western Pacific, transitioning to multiregional activity as the virus travelled. Europe has significantly decreased. The Americas region continues to increase, as does South East Asia, which surpassed the Eastern Mediterranean and European regions today in terms of daily newly confirmed cases; the African region is noticeably increasing as well. The Americas region continues to greatly outnumber all other regions for daily reporting. - Mod.MPP]

